Blindarte is an Italian action house specialised in art. It was founded in 1999 in Naples by Guglielmo Grilli, who is also the artistic director.
In 2004 Blindarte opened a storefront contemporary art gallery above its subterranean offices, soon to be expanded with a series of upper-level exhibition spaces.
In 2009, Blindhouse-Blindarte, a company working in the field of the professional custody of works of art and valuable objects, start to cooperate with the Montepaschi Group in order to manage services and investments connected to the art world.
